Review Text: Nice place to sit, slightly less touristy than I was expecting from the location, which was nice. Three, yes three, cider options: Orchard Thieves, Blind Pig and Old Moot. The bourbon and blueberry Blind Pig is always good for a small …

Name: Proust
Review Text: Best burger I've had in a long time. Good view of the canal with sun streaming in through the south facing window. Terrace seating outside was so busy (for good reason) that we couldn't get a seat, but the interior was equally nice. Good service. Look out for oversized gun chandelier.

Name: Proust
Review Text: So romantic. Hotspot with locals. I recommend it for their beers, chardonnay and biterballen  (Dutch snacking). The little terrasse is lovely in front of the church and the canal.

Name: Proust
Review Text: I had the spicy Burger and the apple pie. It was great! I asked the staff for food and beer recommendations and they did not disappoint. Try the local beers.

Name: Proust
Review Text: Just got into town after a long travel day and found this little place to eat, good food, friendly service, cozy atmosphere, I would recommend!
